The paper deals with generative adversarial networks (GANs) for image-to-image translation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves optimizing the most important convolution filters in the generator networks, which is a task related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves optimization and evolutionary algorithms, which are related to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
